nvh:
entry: able
  partOfSpeech: adjective
  flag: ok
  sense: If someone is able to do something, they can do it.
    example: I'm busy tomorrow, so I won't be able to see you.
      example_translation: Ich habe morgen viel zu tun, deshalb kann ich dich nicht sehen.
        example_lang: German
    translation: fähig
      lang: German
title: able

nvh:
entry: arm
  partOfSpeech: noun
  flag: to_check
  sense: One of the upper limbs, from shoulder to wrist.
    example: You have very long arms.
      example_translation: Sie haben sehr lange Arme.
        example_lang: German
    translation: Arm
      lang: German
  sense: A weapon
    example: The arms dealer was arrested.
      example_translation:Der Waffenhändler wurde verhaftet.
        example_lang: German
    translation: Waffen
      lang: German
title: arm

nvh:
entry: ask
  partOfSpeech: verb
  flag: ok
  sense: To look for an answer to a question.
    example: I need to ask you a question.
      example_translation: Ich muss Ihnen eine Frage stellen.
        example_lang: German
    example: I don't know, ask your mother.
      example_translation: Ich weiß es nicht, frag deine Mutter.
        example_lang: German
    translation: fragen
      lang: German
  sense: To talk to someone to see if they will do something.
    example: She asked me to help her.
      example_translation: Sie bat mich, ihr zu helfen.
        example_lang: German
    example: We will have to ask for more money.
      example_translation: Wir werden mehr Geld beantragen müssen.
        example_lang: German
    translation: bitten
      lang: German
title: ask
